# Design Philosophy

## Complexity vs Feasibility

Do not take shortcuts because the first version is complicated. Take shortcuts only when the full solution is non-feasible (money, time, resource constraints).

If a feature requires a complex implementation to be done correctly, build it correctly. "Too complex for v1" is not a valid reason to cut corners on architecture or security. The valid reasons are:

- The cost is prohibitive (infrastructure, third-party services)
- The timeline doesn't allow it (ship date, dependency on unreleased platform features)
- The team doesn't have the expertise and can't acquire it in time

When proposing a simpler alternative, frame it in terms of feasibility, not difficulty.
